en released and is now available online. In this phase, each beneficiary family will be given an assistance of Rs. 1000 through the payment phase I. This amount will be given by the Labour and Employment Department of the Govt. of Rajasthan. People can check it following the simple steps shared as under:-A) As shown in the figure above, click at the 1st link at COVID-19 homepage at Jan-Soochna Portal (number 1). This link is \u201c\u0915\u094b\u0935\u093f\u0921-19 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0939 \u0930\u093e\u0936\u093f \u092d\u0941\u0917\u0924\u093e\u0928-I (1000 \u0930\u0941\u092a\u092f\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u093f\u0938\u094d\u0924) COVID-19 Ex-gratia Payment-I (Instalment of Rs 1000)\u201c.B) Hit the link to open the COVID-19 Ex-gratia payment 1 status finding page as shown below:-Rajasthan Covid-19 Ex-gratia Payment 1C) Here select the name of the district and municipality for urban areas. However, you will have to select the name of district, panchayat samiti and gram panchayat for rural areas. Then click at the \u201c\u0916\u094b\u091c\u0947\u0902\u201d tab to open the COVID-19 Anugrah Bhugtan Rashi List 1 as shown below:-Rajasthan Covid-19 Anugrah Rashi Bhugtan List 1D) This list contains the name of the district, panchayat samiti, gram panchayat, village, number of beneficiaries, benefited people, failed / declined transaction status. People can even click at the \u201c\u0905\u0927\u093f\u0915 \u091c\u093e\u0928\u0915\u093e\u0930\u0940\u201d tab.Rajasthan Coronavirus Ex Gratia Payment Status 1st ListE) Finally, the list of the all the beneficiaries showing payment statement and other details will appear.Rajasthan COVID-19 Ex-Gratia Payment List 2 (Rs. 1,500 Installment)The Rajasthan Corona Anugrah Rashi Bhugtan list 2 of beneficiaries has been released and is now available online. In this phase, each beneficiary family will be given an assistance of Rs. 1500 through the payment phase II. This amount will be given by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department of the Govt. of Rajasthan. People can check it following the simple steps shared as under:-A) As shown on the Rajasthan Corona Sahayata Yojana payment status checking page, click at the 2nd link at COVID-19 homepage at Jan-Soochna Portal (number 2). This link is \u201c\u0915\u094b\u0935\u093f\u0921-19 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0939 \u0930\u093e\u0936\u093f \u092d\u0941\u0917\u0924\u093e\u0928-II (1500 \u0930\u0941\u092a\u092f\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u093f\u0938\u094d\u0924) COVID-19 Ex-gratia Payment-II (Instalment of Rs 1500)\u201c.B) Hit the link to open the COVID-19 Ex-gratia payment 2 status finding page as shown below:-Rajasthan Covid-19 Ex-Gratia Payment 2nd ListC) Here select the name of the district and municipality for urban areas. However, you will have to select the name of district, panchayat samiti and gram panchayat for rural areas. Then click at the \u201c\u0916\u094b\u091c\u0947\u0902\u201d tab to open the COVID-19 Anugrah Bhugtan Rashi List 2 as shown below:-Rajasthan Covid-19 Anugrah Rashi Bhugtan List 2D) This list contains the name of the district, panchayat samiti, gram panchayat, village, number of beneficiaries, benefited people, failed / declined transaction status. People can even click at the \u201c\u0905\u0927\u093f\u0915 \u091c\u093e\u0928\u0915\u093e\u0930\u0940\u201d tab.Rajasthan Coronavirus Ex-gratia Payment Status 2nd ListE) Finally, the list of the all the beneficiaries showing payment statement and other details will appear.Around 30 lakh households of the Rajasthan state are projected to be benefited by this Rajasthan Corona Sahayata Scheme. The identification of beneficiaries has been done by the respective departments of the state government. Therefore, there is no online / offline application process for enrollment under this scheme. The government will identify the beneficiaries on the basis of Jan Dhan accounts in the state also through other government records.Eligibility Criteria for Rajasthan Corona Sahayata YojanaThe following people comes under the purview of Rajasthan Corona Sahayata beneficiaries under Covid-19 ex-gratia payment scheme-1) All the families falling under BPL, State, BPL and Anatyodaya household category not having any social security pension benefit.2) Registered Constructions labourers who are not include in the above-mentioned category.3) Street vendors who are not included in the two aforesaid categories4) Other Labourers, Rikshaw puller, destitute and other needy people of the state. Moreover, people can click at the number 3 option on the Rajasthan Corona Sahayata Yojana payment status checking page as shown in the figure in 1st section.Rajasthan COVID-19 Information Portal / RajCovidInfo App DownloadRajasthan government has launched COVID-19 Information portal which can be accessed at https://covidinfo.rajasthan.gov.in/. People can even download RajCovidInfo Mobile App from the google play store.Due to nationwide lockdown, the poor section of the state is worst affected as they do not have any source of earning. To provide assistance, the state govt. of Rajasthan comes up with a scheme to help the poor and needy people during these corona crisis. With this Rajasthan Corona Sahayata Yojana, government is making sure that no, person in the state sleeps hungry.An Overview of Rajasthan Covid 19 Anugrah Rashi Bhugtan YojanaHere is an overview of the Rajasthan Corona Sahayata Yojana as mentioned in the table below:-Name of the SchemeRajasthan Covid 19 Ex-Gratia Payment Scheme (\u0930\u093e\u091c\u0938\u094d\u0925\u093e\u0928 \u0915\u094b\u0935\u093f\u0921-19 \u0905\u0928\u0941\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0939 \u0930\u093e\u0936\u093f \u092d\u0941\u0917\u0924\u093e\u0928)State NameRajasthanConcerned DepartmentLabour and Employment Department (1st) and Social Justice and Empowerment Department (2nd), Govt. of IndiaStart date for implementation of scheme25 March 2020Type of assistanceOne-time ex-gratia paymentPayment AmountRs.2500 (1000 + 1500)